      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>2935</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:number>8.2.5</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is proper.
    If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\colon  Y\to  X]]></fr:tex> is a surjective proper morphism, with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> smooth, then the weight-<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> quotient of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(X,\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex> is the image of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(X,\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(Y,\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>.
    The sequence

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2783</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>8.2.5.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {H}^n(X,\mathbb {Q})         \to  \operatorname {H}^n(Y,\mathbb {Q})         \xrightarrow {\operatorname {pr}_1^*-\operatorname {pr}_2^*} \operatorname {H}^n(Y\times _X Y,\mathbb {Q})       \tag{8.2.5.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    is exact.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2784</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">#253</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-253.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:authors /></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> be as in <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.1.1" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.1.1.xml" taxon="Equation" number="8.2.1.1" />, with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_0=Y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_\bullet =\overline {Y}_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>.
      By (ii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.20" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.20.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.1.20" />, we have an exact sequence

      <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2785</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>8.2.5.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           0           \to  \operatorname {H}^n(X,\mathbb {Q})/W^{n-1}\operatorname {H}^n(X,\mathbb {Q})           \to  \operatorname {H}^n(Y_0,\mathbb {Q})           \underset {\delta _1}{\overset {\delta _0}{\rightrightarrows }} \operatorname {H}^n(Y_1,\mathbb {Q})         \tag{8.2.5.2}         ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

      which implies <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.2.5" /> (conversely, this exact sequence can easily be deduced from <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.5.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.2.5" /> and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.7" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.2.7.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="8.2.7" /> below).</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
  
</fr:mainmatter>
